<html
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
    i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-details" />
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-milestones" />
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
    <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-actions" />
</metal:rightportlets>

  <!-- This page uses the launchpad-addform.pt METAL -->

    <div metal:fill-slot="main">

      <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_addform/addform">

        <div metal:fill-slot="extra_info" class="documentDescription">
            A Milestone is a way of targeting a bunch of features and bug
            fixes during your development cycle. Give a simple but
            descriptive name, and if you have a date in mind, fill that in
            below too.
        </div>

        <div class="row" metal:fill-slot="extra_top" tal:replace="nothing">
            <div class="label">Extra top</div>
            <div class="label"><input type="text" style="width:100%" /></div>
            <div>Put any extra form elements you want for this form which
            are not autogenerated here, and they will be at the top of the
            form. The auto-generated elements will use the layout from
            launchpad-widget-macros.pt so try to follow that pattern.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="row"
            metal:fill-slot="extra_bottom" tal:replace="nothing">
          <div class="label">Extra bottom</div>
          <div class="field"><input type="text" style="width:100%" /></div>
          <div>If you want additional non-autogenerated widgets on the firm,
          add them here, as for the set above.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="row" metal:fill-slot="extra_buttons" tal:replace="nothing">
          If you wish to add some more buttons to the form, put those here.
        </div>

      </div>

    <div tal:replace="nothing">This piece will appear at the bottom of the
         form if you want to add a footer.</div>

    </div>
    
  </body>

</html>

